// Stack is a linear abstract data structure. It followa the LIFO (Last In First Out) principle,
//Where the element inserted last is removed first.

// ADS - means what operation a ds can do but not how it is implemented internally. 

//  we can Stack Implementation  using two way:

 
1. Stack Implemmetation using array
2. Stack Implementation using Linked List

// Operation of stacks 
1. push(int data) - to insert a new elements on the top in the stack .
2. pop() - to remove every toppest element of the stack .
3. top() / peek() - return the top element.
4. isEmpty() - return true, if stack is empty. 
5. size() - return the total number of element in the stack.


Time complexity : all operation has o(1).
